HEADWORD: Inturgescence
<hw>In`tur*ges"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inturgescens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>inturgescere</ets> to swell up.
See 1st <er>In-</er>, and <er>Turgescent</er>.]</ety> <def>A swelling;
the act of swelling, or state of being swelled.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
